hwUserLogMIB.description: The A3COM-HUAWEI-USERLOG-MIB contains objects to Manage configuration and Monitor running state for userlog feature.

hwUserlogNatVersion.name: hwUserlogNatVersion
hwUserlogNatVersion.description: NAT LOG version. Currently only version 1 is developed.

hwUserlogNatSyslog.name: hwUserlogNatSyslog
hwUserlogNatSyslog.description: NAT LOG format. If 1, LOG format is sysLog. If 0, LOG format is UDP packet. UDP packet is the default format, and is recommended.

hwUserlogNatSourceIP.name: hwUserlogNatSourceIP
hwUserlogNatSourceIP.description: The Source IP address of NAT LOG UDP packet.

hwUserlogNatFlowBegin.name: hwUserlogNatFlowBegin
hwUserlogNatFlowBegin.description: Log the NAT flow when it is created. If 1, this function is enabled. If 0, this function is disabled. This function will be used when real-time monitor required.

hwUserlogNatActiveTime.name: hwUserlogNatActiveTime
hwUserlogNatActiveTime.description: The active time for long-time existed NAT flow. Unit: minute. Range: 10 minutes ~ 120 minutes. When setting it, NAT flow can be logged after an interval of active time. This function will be used when real-time monitor required. The default value 0 means real-time monitor function is disabled.

hwUserlogNatSlotCfgInfoTable.description: A table of NAT LOG configuration information for the specified slot.

hwUserlogNatSlotCfgInfoEntry.name: hwUserlogNatSlotCfgInfoEntry
hwUserlogNatSlotCfgInfoEntry.description: NAT LOG Configuration Information Entry for a slot.

hwUserlogNatCfgSlotNumber.name: hwUserlogNatCfgSlotNumber
hwUserlogNatCfgSlotNumber.description: Slot number. Specify which slot is configured with NAT LOG.

hwUserlogNatEnable.name: hwUserlogNatEnable
hwUserlogNatEnable.description: The NAT LOG feature Enable status. If 1, NAT LOG is enbled. If 0, NAT LOG is disabled.

hwUserlogNatAclNumber.name: hwUserlogNatAclNumber
hwUserlogNatAclNumber.description: Access-list number. The value 0 means no ACL is specified. Only when NAT LOG is enabled, can ACL be configured. Only NAT flow which match the ACL will be logged.

hwUserlogNatHostAddress.name: hwUserlogNatHostAddress
hwUserlogNatHostAddress.description: The IP address of NAT LOG server.

hwUserlogNatUdpPort.name: hwUserlogNatUdpPort
hwUserlogNatUdpPort.description: The UDP Port Number of NAT LOG UDP packet.

hwUserlogNatRunSlotNumber.description: Slot number. Specify on which slot the NAT LOG statistics displayed.

hwUserlogNatTotalEntries.name: hwUserlogNatTotalEntries
hwUserlogNatTotalEntries.description: The total number of NAT flow entries which are logged.

hwUserlogNatTotalPackets.name: hwUserlogNatTotalPackets
hwUserlogNatTotalPackets.description: The total number of NAT LOG UDP packets generated by the router.

hwUserlogNatFailedEntries.name: hwUserlogNatFailedEntries
hwUserlogNatFailedEntries.description: The total number of NAT flow entries failed in outputting.

hwUserlogNatClearRunStat.name: hwUserlogNatClearRunStat
hwUserlogNatClearRunStat.description: Clear the running statistics for NAT LOG. Write-only. If 1, the running statistics for NAT LOG is resetted. Other value is invalid.
